data.description:
Tuesday March 13, 2019, miami Dade County Public School Board Members unanimously approved Human Trafficking Education in Schools Policy.

School Board Member Dr Dorothy Bendross Mindingall proposed Item H-12 Human Trafficking Education Requesting to add Human Trafficking component to the health curriculum in schools. All School Board Members voted in its favor.

In addition, a letter will be sent to Tallahassee Legislative  Bill Sponsors expressing the School Board’s support of HB259/SB982 Human Trafficking Education in Schools.
